<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870924-0120 </DOCNO><HL> Laidlaw Adams Changes Name</HL><DD> 09/24/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> SECURITIES INDUSTRY (SCR) </IN><DATELINE> NEW YORK  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Laidlaw, Adams andamp; Peck Inc., a closely held securities firm, said it changed its name to Kuhns Brothers andamp; Laidlaw Inc. to reflect its new ownership.    In September 1986, a New York investor group, led by John D. Kuhns, paid $4 million to acquire a majority stake in the firm. Mr. Kuhns, who became chairman, formerly was president and chief executive officer of Catalyst Energy Development Corp., a New York owner of power plants and other energy producers. </TEXT></DOC>